<lb />3) a chap, fellow: <cit><quote>this is a riddling m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 3, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what saucy m. was this, that was so full of his ropery?</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 153</bibl></cit>.
